<br>
First off, the setup and assumptions:<br>
<br>
Since you have to be lvl 51 to use the robe, we'll use that as a reference level.<br>
<br>
To my knowledge, your medding mana regen rate is <br>
<br>
meditation / 12 = mana per tick<br>
Could be wrong, but that's what I last saw.<br>
<br>
Level 51 mage has a meditate skill of 238.<br>
<br>
The robe converts 60hps to 20mana with a 3 sec casting time and no recast. You must be standing to use the robe obviously so your natural mana regen standing will be 1 mana per tick for this reference, assuming you don't hammer click the robe to make sure you start casting immediately after the inital cast, we'll say 1 cast = 4sec<br>
<br>
so here we go:<br>
<br>
Regular sitting/medding = 238 / 12 = 20 mana / 6 sec = 200 mana per min.<br>
<br>
Mana robe = 20 mana / 4 sec + 1 mana / 6 sec = 300mana / min + 60mana / min  = 360 mana per min<br>
<br>
Mana robe on a horse = 300mana / min + 200mana / min = 500mana / min<br>
<br>
So there you go, a mathmatical analysis for 1min of robe clicking vs 1min of medding. Now when you toss in FT items and spells/buffs it will go that much higher. I can only see the advantage of the mana robe when used on a horse. One thing you have to keep in mind, 1 min of solid robe clicks(15) will drain the mage of 900hps.<br>
<br>
Hope this at least sheds some light on stuff. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=465781">Master Nucci</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
